            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EWant%20to%20know%20why%20you%20should%20be%20a%20witness%20for%20Jesus%20Christ%3F%20Because%20He%20died%20for%20all%2C%20and%20therefore%2C%20all%20died.%20Because%20you%20died%20with%20Christ%2C%20you%20should%20no%20longer%20live%20for%20yourself%20(2%20Corinthians%205%3A15).%20Because%20you%20no%20longer%20live%20for%20yourself%2C%20you%20are%20no%20longer%20the%20same%20person%20you%20were.%20%22What%20this%20means%20is%20that%20those%20who%20become%20Christians%20become%20new%20persons.%20They%20are%20not%20the%20same%20anymore%2C%20for%20the%20old%20life%20is%20gone.%20A%20new%20life%20has%20begun%22%20(v.%2017)!%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EGod%20has%20given%20you%2C%20as%20a%20%22new%20creation%22%20believer%2C%20the%20task%20of%20reconciling%20people%20to%20Him%20(v.%2018).%20Your%20message%20of%20reconciliation%20is%20this%3A%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%22For%20God%20was%20in%20Christ%2C%20reconciling%20the%20world%20to%20himself%2C%20no%20longer%20counting%20people's%20sins%20against%20them.%20This%20is%20the%20wonderful%20message%20he%20has%20given%20us%20to%20tell%20others%22%20(v.%2019).%20Legally%2C%20the%20world%20has%20already%20been%20forgiven%20in%20Christ%3B%20thus%2C%20your%20job%20is%20to%20be%20His%20ambassador%2C%20imploring%20people%20on%20Christ's%20behalf%20to%20be%20reconciled%20to%20God%20(v.%2020).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20conclusion%3F%20You%20are%20dead%20to%20your%20former%20life%20and%20thus%20unconcerned%20about%20public%20opinion.%20You%20live%20only%20to%20inform%20the%20lost%20that%20Jesus%20reconciled%20them%20to%20God.%20Some%20will%20receive%2C%20some%20will%20reject%2C%20but%20all%20must%20be%20told.%20That%2C%20dear%20ambassador%2C%20is%20your%20mission!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
